feat(briefing): approval queue + live autonomy tiers; scheduler infra e2e

M07 Step 5 + Step 4 Part B — closes Stage 7.

Part A — approval queue + live autonomy tiers
- BriefingItem approve/edit/skip live behind BearerAuthGuard on the
  briefing controller.
- Approving a Yellow item mints a single-use ApprovalToken bound to
  (userId, action, payloadHash); M01 capability-gate verifies +
  consumes it once; replay is denied.
- Per-user UserSettings.autonomyDefaults[action] TIGHTENS the registry
  tier live end-to-end via a UserAutonomyResolver consulted by the
  gate-interceptor BEFORE enforce(). Green->Yellow requires a token;
  Green->Red is uncallable even with a valid token.
- Immutable audit log covers every allow/deny; GET /v1/audit exposes it.
- Tests: approval.handlers (10), audit.handlers (6),
  autonomy-tier.live (5) — all green.

Part B — scheduler infra e2e (closes the Step-4 gap)
- Redis-backed IdempotencyStore adapter (SET NX EX 48h).
- BullMQ briefing-scheduler queue + worker over runOvernightLoop.
- e2e against real docker Redis: trigger -> one BriefingRun; N=8
  CONCURRENT duplicate triggers -> EXACTLY ONE composer invocation;
  research->plan hook regenerates on HIGH-impact findings with diff;
  quiet-hours suppression holds with the real scheduler.

